measures.name: net_zero_k_12_fenestration_and_daylighting_controls
measures.display_name: Net Zero K12 - Fenestration and Daylighting Controls
measures.description: This measure will remove all existing exterior windows, glass doors, and skylights from your model. They will be replaced with view and daylight windows as recommended by the Net Zero K12 recommendations. Windows on the south facade will have a exterior shading or light shelf surfaces depending on if they are view or daylight windows. East and west view windows will have internal shading controls. In spaces with daylighting controls daylight sensor will be added. The modeler should inspect where the sensors were placed, the recommended illuminance setpoint, and the fraction of the zones lighting controlled by the sensor.
measures.modeler_description: This measure is intended for use in models created form space types defined in the primary and secondary building types. Other space types used in the model will not receive any new fenestration, however fenestration will be removed from all space types. Attic and plenum spaces will not receive any new fenestration. Daylighting will only be added to north and south facades. North and south facades can be +/- 30 degrees of north and south. East and west facades will only receive view windows. Mechanical rooms won't relieve any view or daylight windows. Kitchens and Restrooms wont' receive any view windows. Toplighting will not be added.In sidelight spaces the sensor's depth in from the wall will typically be the same as the height of the wall that the daylight windows is on. This depth is also what is used to calculate the daylight fraction of the space. In spaces that are non convex, such as an L shaped space, we may not be able to place a sensor, if that happens a warning will be issued.

da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Customized values for ZEDG - This measure removes all existing electric equipment from spaces recognized as primary or secondary school space types. da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Ext Wall
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, currently only set for steel frame walls. This measure will modify existing exterior wall insulation levels based on construction type and climate zone. The exterior wall construction type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. For mass and metal walls if an existing insulation layer can be found it will be increased, if not a new insulation layer will be added. For mass this will be at the exterior of the construction. For metal it will be added just behind the exterior layer. For steel and wood framed walls, insulation will be added to the exterior of the construction.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Roof
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: ZEDG version, only setup for IEAD roof. This measure will modify existing roof insulation levels and Solar Reflective Index (SRI) values based on roof type and climate zone. The roof type and climate zone should be set in the model prior to using this measure. If your model uses an attic, all attic surfaces should have an "Attic' intended surface type. For attics it doesn't matter what you put for "Standards Construction Type". The measure will check attic insulation where the attic is adjacent to other not attic spaces.

da_descriptions.name: ZEDG Fenistration with Daylighting
da_descriptions.description: Option 2 Description: This measure will remove all existing exterior windows, glass doors, and skylights from your model. They will be replaced with view and daylight windows as recommended by the Net Zero K12 recommendations. Windows on the south facade will have a exterior shading or light shelf surfaces depending on if they are view or daylight windows. East and west view windows will have internal shading controls. In spaces with daylighting controls daylight sensor will be added. The modeler should inspect where the sensors were placed, the recommended illuminance setpoint, and the fraction of the zones lighting controlled by the sensor.
